transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I want to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me pull up your information there and see if I can help you with that.

Speaker 2: I'm pretty sure I can. Give me one second.

Speaker 1: Trying to pull you up with your phone number. Is this Bruce I'm speaking to?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: All right, Bruce. I do have you up. I'm looking at your account.

Speaker 2: I do see that you're currently getting the Viagra 50 milligrams.

Speaker 1: It looks like that you're getting 40 of them every three months.

Speaker 2: Can I ask you any reason why you want to cancel, Bruce, if you don't mind?

Speaker 1: Yeah, because I'm just not using them.

Speaker 2: Okay, not a problem. I see you're getting a large quantity there, too.

Speaker 1: What I can do for you, Bruce, to help you out here to keep your subscription.

Speaker 2: No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no. Just cancel my subscription, please.

Speaker 1: Okay, not a problem. We're going to cancel. I do have to tell you, by you cancelling your subscription,

Speaker 2: that means you will not be able to order from us in the future because we do have to have a prescription on file.

Speaker 1: That's why I was just going to recommend that we can still postpone it.

Speaker 2: It's fine. It's fine. No problem.

Speaker 1: All right. I'll go ahead and take care of that for you.

Speaker 2: I do see you just had an order recently shipped out to you, and I will stop all future orders going out.

Speaker 1: How are the pills working for you? I'm just curious, the 50 milligrams, when you were using them.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so I don't even know if I used any of them.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Not a problem. So I went ahead and took care of that for you, Bruce.

Speaker 2: Unfortunately, because we are on a first-come, first-served basis, and we typically are sold out for any canceled prescriptions

Speaker 1: because we only take care of our prescriptions that are active and any new orders.

Speaker 2: So if you did in the future want to order, we've got to tell you to order from us.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: I'm good. I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: All right. Not a problem. I'll just take care of it for you. You're all done.

Speaker 2: Thanks a lot.

Speaker 1: All right. Have a good one.

Speaker 2: Thanks. Bye. You too.
